    <svcsubproc id="x204011104">
        <title>Stabilizer Bar and Link Removal and Installation</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Suspension fasteners are critical parts because they affect performance of vital parts and systems
                    and their failure can result in major service expense. A new part with the same part number must be
                    installed if installation becomes necessary. Do not use a replacement part of lesser quality or
                    substitute design. Torque values must be used as specified during reassembly to make sure of correct
                    retention of these parts.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Raise and support the vehicle. For additional information, refer to
                <exhotlnk document="../S10/S10019.htm" bookname="S10019">Jacking and Lifting in S10019</exhotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the nuts, bolts, brackets and the stabilizer bar links.</para>
            <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 90 Nm (66 Lbf-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0401026" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020562.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the nuts, bolts, brackets and the front stabilizer bar.</para>
            <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 90 Nm (66 Lbf-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0401027" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020611.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To install, reverse the removal procedure.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
